RACE.FOOTNOTES: HADDASSAH had a ideal set up by oneself watching the engaged pair down the backside, waited to pounce on the fence through the turn, had a clear lane five wide two furlongs from the line, opened up to clear drifting in under right handed urging at the furlong pole and was kept to the task to win comfortably at the finish. ELUSIVE KNIGHT relaxed trailing the field down the backstretch, began to creep closer to the field gaining momentum at the seven sixteenths marker, swung out widest in the nine path full of run straightening out for the stretch drive, chased the winner in vain late besting the rest for a clear second. MIDNIGHT IN MALIBU settled outside near the rear in the early going, moved smartly around foes four wide progressing on the turn, swung out to the eight path for the drive to the wire to have a share of the lead in upper stretch and finished with intent to be a solid third crossing the line. DANCIN IN DA'NILE was alone in the third flight down the back straight, rated kindly on the turn, sat behind a wall of runners six wide for the stretch drive, shifted in going for a seam in the three path with three sixteenths to go, weaved between foes and got up for a minor role in the end. BODE'S TIPSY ducked inwards sharply leaving the chute, recovered quickly to improve to midpack switching outside three deep at the half, tracked in the second flight two wide outside on the turn, ran gamely to be in the hunt in the six path at the quarter pole but faded late drifting in at the sixteenth pole. BRITISH ROYALTY settled near the rear on the fence in the beginning, offered a good turn of foot running between foes with three eighths remaining, had a clear path three wide at the top of the lane, could not accelerate quick enough, lost the seam inside the three sixteenths marker, was then steadied on the fence and could not recover to be involved at the finish. TOP OF THE CHARTS travelled in the middle of the pack on the rail, saved ground keeping up with rivals through the turn, try to rally on the fence with a quarter to go, was in tight inside at the three sixteenths marker, had nowhere to run, shifted outside in the two path late and could not be a factor at the finish. KEROUAC took this field down the backside, maintained a slim advantage running on the turn, could not find more turning for home and was swallowed up by the closing pack in mid -stretch. MAD MOCHA hopped at the break, prompted outside down the back straight, pressed the pace two wide throughout the turn, poked his head in front momentarily at the top of the lane and stopped between rivals with three sixteenths to run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOKES UP broke inwards at the start, had a good position watching the contesting duo at the half, waited to pounce under a snug hold throughout the turn, took control outside at the furlong marker and had enough left to hold safe late for the win. KANTBACKOFF was forced inside to start, waited behind runners when the field bunched up at the three furlong marker, was nudged on the maintain position between horses at the quarter pole, bullied her way through in the three path with an eighth to go and was gaining strongly late but could not get there in time. ONDINE LADY pressed the issue up front down the backstretch on the fence, slipped through on the rail three furlongs from home, opened up mildly at the quarter pole, gave way to the fast closing winner with a sixteenth remaining and faded late to dead heat for third money in the end. HITS DIFFERENT was pushed in at the start, tracked the top three on the rail down the backside, was scrubbed on for more run midpoint on the turn, never gave up and gamely fought on with rivals on each side to close in to capture third in a dead heat at the finish. TALKING WONDERS was bumped on the break trailing down the backside, caught up to the field moving well on the fence at the three furlong marker, was checked on the rail with a quarter to go, stubbornly re-rallied inside for the stretch drive but stalled in the last sixteenth. NEOLITHIC NATION travelled four deep near the back in the beginning, made little progress throughout the turn and finished mildly down the stretch. GUNNAWIN settled near the rear three deep early on, could not keep up with rallying horses with five sixteenths to go, swung outside runners four wide at the quarter pole, continued shifting outwards to be widest in lane eight for the drive and had no finish to give running to the wire. CANTHO stalked in midpack three wide outside horses down the back straight, was hard ridden trying to go after the leaders midway on the turn, had a chance for a small share between foes at the top of the lane but levelled off at the furlong marker. SEATTLE SIGNAL set the pace down the backstretch just off the rail, surrendered the lead in the two path with three eighths to go, gave way getting out five to six wide at the quarter pole and retreated in upper stretch.
